openUrlModal

public void openUrlModal(String url,
                         boolean showNavigationControls)
Opens a URL in another UIViewController/Activity that contains a UIWebView/WebView, a close button, a back button, a forward button, and an open externally (in Safari, eg) button. Note that only one of these views may be present at once, i.e. if openUrlModal(url) is called and the event .modalBrowserClosed is never raised (regardless of presence of listeners), then any subsequent openUrlModal(url) calls are ignored and an .error.modalBrowserCouldNotBeOpened event is raised.

Parameters:
url - String url to open
showNavigationControls - boolean a flag indicating if back, forwards and open externally buttons are visible

public void closeModalBrowser()
Closes the UIViewController/Activity that contains the webpage (if any) that .openUrlModal(url) opened. If there is no page to close, then an events.error.modalBrowserWasNotOpened event is raised but no action is performed.

public String url()

precacheVideo

public void precacheVideo(String url)
Precaches (but does not play) the video passed into the params. The video may be played by calling .play() after the .event.precached event is received (noting that the video was successfully preached). Playing the video before it is precached will result in the video playing.

Parameters:
url - String the URL of the video to preached

setCurrentTime

public void setCurrentTime(int time)
Scrubs the video to the passed time. If the time is invalid (time < 0 or time > .duration()), then the .events.error.couldNotSetTime event is raised. If the time is valid, the video playhead location is reset to the passed time and the .events.timeUpdate event must be raised. Additionally, .currentTime() should reflect the time passed into .setCurrentTime(time) (i.e. .setCurrentTime(.currentTime()) would have no effect).

Parameters:
time - int to set

play

public void play()
Plays the video from the current playhead location. If .currentTime() = 0, the .events.started event is raised.

pause

public void pause()
Plays the video from the current playhead location. If .currentTime() = 0, the .events.started event is raised.

stop

public void stop()
Stops the video and resets the playhead to 0. Raises the .events.unpaused event and the .events.timeUpdate event, reflecting the playhead move to 0.
